These are some references I would like to push upstream to the Go community
for consideration in their evoluation of Go exception-handling structures.

https://books.google.com/books/about/Program_Structures_for_Exceptional_Condi.html?id=JWIZAQAAIAAJ
https://www.worldcat.org/title/program-structures-for-exceptional-condition-handling/oclc/123148767

http://www.scielo.br/pdf/jbcos/v10n3/02.pdf
https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/A-Study-of-the-Applicability-of-Existing-Techniques-Lang-Stewart/714a2dbbeda0d1ce17a9d8cdc387cb1a3c713fd1
https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/An-exception-handling-model-for-parallel-and-its-Issarny/2af2c9a388845518a13535a455ecf205f26d7ccf
https://www.researchgate.net/publication/282571900_Cooperative_Exceptions_for_Concurrent_Objects

Advances in Exception Handling Techniques
edited by Alexander Romanovsky, Christophe Dony, Jorgen Lindskov Knudsen, Anand Tripathi

Advanced Topics in Exception Handling Techniques
edited by Christophe Dony, Jorgen Lindskov Knudsen, Alexander Romanovsky, Anand Tripathi

